
.ad l

.ll 72

.ce 1000
\fBcursor.hint()\fR
.ce 0

.sp 2

.SH "NAME"
\fBNAME\fR
.sp 2
hint - Visit result set using specified index.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBSYNOPSIS\fR
.sp 2

.sp 2

.sp 2
cousor.hint(\fB[hint]\fR)
.SH "CATEGORY"
\fBCATEGORY\fR
.sp 2

.sp 2
Cursor
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBDESCRIPTION\fR
.sp 2
Visit result set using specified index.
.sp 2
\fBhint (json object)\fR
.br
         It specifies the visiting plan to accelarate query
         speed.
.sp 2
         \fBFormat\fR
.br
                  The method "cursor.hint()" contains parameter
                  "hint". If it is not specified, the query will
                  not use index to visit records. The parameter
                  "hint" contain a one-field json object. The
                  field name is ignored. But the field value is
                  specified as the index which will be visited.
                  When it is null, it will visit all the records
                  in the collection.
.br
                  {"":null} or {"":"<indexname>"}
.SH "Examples"
\fBExamples\fR
.sp 2
Find records that contains the field "age" in the collection
"bar" using the index "ageIndex" and return results.
.sp 2
db.foo.bar.find({age:{$exists:1}}).hint({"":"ageIndex"})
.sp 2
\fBRelated information\fR
.br
cursor.sort()
.br
cursor.limit()
.br
db.collectionspace.collection.find()